humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae No. III/X,' which means that out of the 10 assessed lymph nodes, 3 were positive for metastases. This corresponds to N1 according to the AJCC staging system (New Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes).

humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae No. III/X', which indicates that cancer has spread to 3 out of the 10 examined axillary lymph nodes. This corresponds to a pathologic N stage of N1.
